    {
      "id": "1ff5a927fad02a3c1213bca5cb820d1a9d601ba2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 257,
        "name": "Keith Mannthey",
        "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
        "username": "kmannth",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-28 19:32:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nI am still not clear as to why most of these areas need the additions.   It is not that I think this code is all lock free safe but I don't see how most of these changes help the local code block. \n\nWe should be very sure that a lock is needed and enforce that across the API. \n\nA commit message or multiple patches that explain why each lock that is used is changed would be very helpful in reviewing this patch as right now most of the spots still look arbitrary and not particularly helpful.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "1cf07d972703952280ad3813fd9d8801a1e6f682",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 160,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sebastien.buisson@bull.net",
        "username": "sebastien.buisson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-31 09:38:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nHi,\nAs explained in the associated Jira ticket, these additions are only proposals. They are based on the statistical analysis made by Coverity. The tool has found out that the accesses to some variables were always protected by a lock, except in the cases where I propose the additions. Again, the proposed additions are only based on this analysis, not on the direct suspicion of a race.\nSo if you think some additions are useless, please explain why and I will remove them from the patch, thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "fa138c5c9c51fe5939d60fc752c13a4a4e5246ac",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 257,
        "name": "Keith Mannthey",
        "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
        "username": "kmannth",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-31 22:20:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: No score\n\nSebastien,  Can you split each lock out so it can be easier to review. There are at least 4 unrelated locks in this single patch. \n\nSome of these spots look like areas that need locking and when this patch is split up it will be easier to address each lock that is changing it's scope.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "39b5c73438c778e0652d70821109325647ca6ee5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 160,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sebastien.buisson@bull.net",
        "username": "sebastien.buisson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-06-06 12:53:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nHi,\n\nTo ease analysis, this patch has been split into 9:\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6567\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6568\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6569\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6570\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6571\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6572\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6573\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6574\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/6575",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
